Class NBServerQueuePolicy

java.lang.Object
  OpenFlow.NBAPI.NBServerQueuePolicy
Direct Known Subclasses:
ControllerContext.CCQueuePolicy
public class NBServerQueuePolicy
extends java.lang.Object

Queue policy context for northbound API access to SDN controller.

Tracks the requested/resulting queue policy context for a northbound API server connection. This context will be updated to reflect the server's actual settings and track changes throughout the connection and these updated values will persist after the connection has been terminated. If no connection exists when a set-value method is called, the context's value is updated immediately. If an established connection exists, a set-value method will (asynchronously) issue an appropriate request to the server and the context values will be updated once the response is received from the server. Thus, the get-value methods will only return the last known server state and not the most recently requested values (if a disconnect occurs before the response is received, the requested values are lost).
